field.value:
I have discovered a weird behavior with the DictHelper.CreateN().N() usage. Values passed to those methods are added to the dictionary as strings. 

This causes a problem when trying to call something like the following:

{code lang=java}
Url.For(Dict.N("action", "ActionName").N("params", Dict.N("id", id)))
{code}
The value inserted for key 'params' is then a string (class name) and not the actual dictionary, which in turn causes UrlBuilder to fail.
